item.title: Santa Fe Ulitmate History Walking Tour
item.description: Get oriented to Santa Fe’s unique history, architecture, and culture on this top-rated walking tour. Explore the Santa Fe plaza area on foot, passing landmarks like the Loretto Chapel, Palace of the Governors, and Bario de Analco, plus places off the beaten path that most visitors miss. Hear stories not found in any guidebook, and get tips on how to make the most of your Santa Fe vacation.

image.alt: Santa Fe Ulitmate History Walking Tour

item.title: New Mexican Flavors Food Tour of the Santa Fe Plaza
item.description: Taste the highlights of Santa Fe during this food-themed walking tour. Meet your guide in the centrally located Santa Fe Plaza, and come hungry: you’ll visit multiple local food businesses, where you can enjoy enough samples to add up to a generous meal (plus drinks on the side). As you go, you’ll also see landmarks like the San Miguel Chapel and the Palace of the Governors.

image.alt: New Mexican Flavors Food Tour of the Santa Fe Plaza

item.title: Santa Fe Revisited
item.description: There are many Santa Fe tours out there, but this is the only one lead by a homegrown historian and author of eight books on the city. Take advantage of the guide’s deep knowledge of Santa Fe history and culture to gain a new perspective on landmarks like the Loretto Chapel, Canyon Road, Cross of the Martyrs, Route 66, and more. The tour delves into topics not often covered, including the Manhattan Project, spirituality, and Santa Fe’s role in World War II.

image.alt: Santa Fe Revisited

item.title: Wander New Mexico Food Tour - Downtown Plaza 'Sip & Savor'
item.description: Explore downtown Santa Fe's best food and wine venues on a half-day walking tour led by an informative guide. Get a taste of new developments in Santa Fe’s food scene and sample classic New Mexican flavors when you stop into several local eateries. You'll also visit landmarks like the Cathedral Basilica of Saint Francis, Loretto Chapel, and Palace of the Governors. Your guide shares commentary about the city’s history and the mix of cultures that have shaped its food culture throughout the leisurely walking tour.

image.alt: Wander New Mexico Food Tour - Downtown Plaza 'Sip & Savor'

item.title: Small-Group E-Bike Adventure Tour through Hidden Santa Fe
item.description: See a different side of Santa Fe beyond the plaza on a fun and athletic e-bike tour that earns rave reviews from travelers. Cover more ground than you would on a walking tour, taking advantage of the bike’s battery-assisted boost to go farther without breaking a sweat. Visit places many tourists miss, like the Santa Fe Railyard and River Park that hugs the Rio Grande, while a guide shares insider history not found in the guidebooks.

image.alt: Small-Group E-Bike Adventure Tour through Hidden Santa Fe

item.title: Santa Fe Architectural Walking Tour
item.description: Santa Fe has architecture unlike nearly any city in the United States—it’s dominated by adobe buildings but has diverse Victorian and Mission Revival styles. This tours offers a chance to learn about the architecture while taking a guided walk through the city’s back roads, residential areas, and art districts. Finish with a champagne tasting at Gruet Tasting Room at Hotel St. Francis.

image.alt: Santa Fe Architectural Walking Tour

item.title: Taste of Santa Fe Wine and Dine Lunch
item.description: Discover Santa Fe’s must-try bites—and learn about the city’s history and culture—on this decadent walking tour. Meet your guide before lunch at Santa Fe Plaza, and come ready with an appetite: you’ll visit three local eateries, where you can enjoy everything from spicy New Mexican fare to tasty local chocolates. As you go, you’ll also see landmarks like the New Mexico State Capitol, Palace of the Governors, and more.

image.alt: Taste of Santa Fe Wine and Dine Lunch

item.title: 2-Hour Photography Class While Touring Downtown Santa Fe, Smart Phones Welcome!
item.description: Santa Fe is a photographer’s dream, so learn how to capture the city’s unique adobe architecture, enchanting desert light, and colorful streets like a pro. A trained photographer and longtime Santa Fe resident takes you to the most photogenic locations around the plaza and helps you get that perfect shot, whether you're working with a high-tech DSLR camera or a smart phone.

image.alt: 2-Hour Photography Class While Touring Downtown Santa Fe, Smart Phones Welcome!

item.title: Viator Exclusive: Gourmet Brunch in Santa Fe with Chef Carolina
item.description: Dining options in Santa Fe can seem endless, so remove the guesswork and start your day with a memorable meal at a specialty chef’s brunch not found at any restaurant. A local chef trained at the famously Le Cordon Bleu culinary school prepares a seasonal meal using high-quality ingredients that showcase Santa Fe’s unique cuisine drawn from Spanish, Mexican, and Native American flavors.

image.alt: Viator Exclusive: Gourmet Brunch in Santa Fe with Chef Carolina

item.title: Santa Fe: Canyon Road Art & History Walking Tour
item.description: Discover Canyon Road, home to over 80 art galleries, on a guided tour through Santa Fe. Walk through a number of exciting galleries to give you a sense of what Canyon Road has to offer. Engage with many of the art pieces and have a chat with the local artists and gallery curators. Your tour is limited to 10 participants, which allows for a more personal experience.

image.alt: Santa Fe: Canyon Road Art & History Walking Tour

item.title: Small Group Santa Fe Walking Tour
item.description:
Ever felt lost in the crowd? Why not enjoy an intimate small group walking tour with us, just 10 people or less. We are Rebecca & Timo, owners and operators of About Santa Fe, your small group tour guides. We personally love taking tours when we travel and we always choose small group tours ourselves. Nothing compares to the interaction that can be had in a small group.
Experience the enchanting allure of downtown Santa Fe through an enlightening exploration of its attractions. Immerse yourself in the city's distinctive history and culture guided by a seasoned local expert. Ease into Santa Fe's elevation as we leisurely stroll through its rich historical sites, while we delve into the nuances of the "City Different." Wander through lesser-known locations and uncover the hidden secrets they hold.
WINTER NOTE: We may cancel tours during the winter if conditions are to cold, windy or considered unsafe dure to ice or blizzard.

image.alt: Small Group Santa Fe Walking Tour

item.title: Creative Soul Scavenger Hunt of Santa Fe
item.description: Explore Santa Fe while having fun with friends and family by signing up for a scavenger hunt of the city. You'll have a host on hand via WhatsApp to provide clues and help you if you run into any problems. Best of all, your hunt is a co-creation between you and your host, who will customize your hunt as you go.

image.alt: Creative Soul Scavenger Hunt of Santa Fe

item.title: Santa Fe Historic Downtown Smart Phone Audio App Self Guided GPS Walking Tour
item.description: The historic Santa Fe Plaza and downtown area has a 400-year old history filled with the lore and legends of conquistadors, scientists, artists, outlaws, and Pueblo peoples. Access this history on your phone through our GPS-enabled walking tour. Start and stop on your own schedule—access to the tour never expires. Learn about the annual Zozobra celebration, what "Christmas-style" means, and where to find the oldest church in the United States.

image.alt: Santa Fe Historic Downtown Smart Phone Audio App Self Guided GPS Walking Tour

item.title: Santa Fe Haunted Spirits Tour
item.description: The highest, oldest capital city in the nation—and one of the oldest US cities, bar none—Santa Fe is littered with ghost stories, haunting tales, colorful characters, and inexplicable events. On this tour, follow your guide downtown, diving deep into the city’s spooky side, diving deep into some of the city’s best cocktails, and diving deep into a history only Santa Fe can offer.

image.alt: Santa Fe Haunted Spirits Tour

item.title: Plaza Sip, Savor, & History Walking Tour in Santa Fe
item.description:
Hosted by tour company Vigilante Guides. As a 12th generation New Mexican we take pride in culture and history and want to share a piece of our everyday life on this tour. This is a fun and informational experience that is all inclusive. We talk about our unique culture and heritage, our amazing food and drink, art and outdoors and everything else in between. This is an experience unlike any other where you truly feel like a local. We have fun, interact, and enjoy each others company while we eat and drink some local delicacies. Oh and yes, come hungry, you should be adequately fed by the end of this tour.
On this tour you will stop at 3 locations and try a variety of craft cocktails, beer, wine, and margaritas along with some amazing pizza and tacos.
We will walk away as friends and show you the true Santa Fe experience.

image.alt: Plaza Sip, Savor, & History Walking Tour in Santa Fe

item.title: The Best of Santa Fe & The Georgia O'Keeffe Museum: Private Tour
item.description: With so much to explore, it can be hard to know where to begin in Santa Fe. This private walking tour removes the guesswork for an ideal introduction to the city’s historic plaza, charming adobe buildings, parks, and art galleries. Finish at the Georgia O'Keeffe Museum, with included admission so you can explore the life of this artist who immortalized northern New Mexico landscapes.

image.alt: The Best of Santa Fe & The Georgia O'Keeffe Museum: Private Tour

item.title: Meow Wolf's House of Eternal Return
item.description:
The original permanent Meow Wolf exhibition, House of Eternal Return is a monumental achievement in DIY world creation and collaboration, featuring over 70 rooms made by local and community artists.
At House of Eternal Return, people of all ages are encouraged to explore a curious family home, a mysterious tragedy born out of scientific experimentation, and the spectacular dreamworlds that have emerged in its wake. Simultaneously an expression of punk subversion and magical humanness, Meow Wolf Santa Fe is an art experience that's boldly playful in its presentation and willingness to reveal the hands of its creators.

image.alt: Meow Wolf's House of Eternal Return

item.title: Railyard Sip, Savor, & History Walking Tour in Santa Fe
item.description: Hosted by tour company Vigilante Guides. As a 12th generation New Mexican we provide a fun and informational experience that is all inclusive. We talk about our unique culture and heritage, our amazing food and drink, art and outdoors and everything else in between. This is an experience unlike any other where you truly feel like a local. We have fun, interact, and enjoy each others company while we eat and drink some local delicacies.

image.alt: Railyard Sip, Savor, & History Walking Tour in Santa Fe

item.title: A Walking Tour of Santa Fe's Most Beautiful and Historic Sites
item.description: Whether it's your first time in Santa Fe or you’d like to delve deeper into the city’s history and legends, make the most out of your time on a private walking tour of must-see highlights plus hidden corners. Learn fascinating trivia and stories as you wander cobblestone streets and colorful alleyways that wind through the downtown plaza area and beyond.

image.alt: A Walking Tour of Santa Fe's Most Beautiful and Historic Sites

item.title: Magic on Canvas Painting Class at Artful Soul Santa Fe
item.description: Unleash your inner creative during a guided art workshop in Santa Fe which is ideal for would-be artists of all ages and levels. Don’t waste time deciding what to create; instead, benefit from your tutor’s informative step-by-step demonstration of your subject matter and take advantage of one-on-one guidance to create a unique piece of art.

image.alt: Magic on Canvas Painting Class at Artful Soul Santa Fe

item.title: Stained Glass Class - Hidden Santa Fe Gem
item.description: Get the chance to break glass and melt metal while creating unique works of art at this stained glass class in Santa Fe. Using straight-forward instruction, your teacher will show you centuries-old techniques of an art form that goes back to the 6th century. You'll make suncatcher ornaments using techniques developed by the famous Tiffany glassmakers. Newbies welcome, and discounts offered for BIPOC.

image.alt: Stained Glass Class - Hidden Santa Fe Gem

item.title: Our Lady of Guadalupe Walking Tour in Santa Fe
item.description:
This one of a kind walking tour will help you understand the significance of Our Lady of Guadalupe in the history of our unique city.
Following on the research I have done, this walking tour tells the story behind about a dozen art installations, murals, and tiles featuring her image.
Have your cameras ready because each stop, planned or not, is an opportunity to capture beautiful images and share them with the hashtag #whereslupita, joining thousands of people worldwide in the documentation of this powerful and iconic image.

image.alt: Our Lady of Guadalupe Walking Tour in Santa Fe

item.title: 2 Hour Pottery Experience (Wheel or Hand-Building)
item.description: There’s nowhere better to try your hand at pottery than Santa Fe, arguably America’s artsiest city. With this experiential class—geared to travelers and newbies—you’ll get one no-strings two-hour session at the wheel, guided by a local pro. Great for friends, families, and anyone interested in getting their hands dirty, you’ll leave the wheel having explored your artistic side.

image.alt: 2 Hour Pottery Experience (Wheel or Hand-Building)

item.title: Savor Santa Fe: Wine Pairing Dinner
item.description: Visit three of Santa Fe’s destination restaurants—and enjoy a gourmet, multi-course dinner, complete with wine pairings—during this local-led food tour. Meet your guide in the late afternoon right in the central Santa Fe Plaza, and come hungry: you’ll visit top-rated restaurants, and will enjoy high-end, New Mexican dishes at each, plus wine and drinks. In between, spy local landmarks and learn about Santa Fe’s history and food culture.

image.alt: Savor Santa Fe: Wine Pairing Dinner
